# Module Dependencies Diagram

This diagram shows the architecture transformation from monolithic God objects
to modular services.

## Metrics Comparison

| Metric                   | Before (Monolithic) | After (Modular) | Improvement    |
| ------------------------ | ------------------- | --------------- | -------------- |
| **extension.ts LOC**     | 1200                | ~800            | -33% (400 LOC) |
| **goferMigrator.ts LOC** | 2499                | 467             | -81% (2032 LOC) |
| **Total God object LOC** | 3699                | 1267            | -66% (2432 LOC) |
| **Service count**        | 2 (monoliths)       | 12 (focused)    | +10 services   |
| **Max service LOC**      | 2499                | 496             | -80%           |
| **Testable units**       | 2                   | 12              | 6x increase    |

## Architecture Principles

### Before: Monolithic (Anti-Patterns)

❌ **God Objects**: Single files with 1000+ LOC and 20+ responsibilities

- `extension.ts`: Initialization + Events + Commands + Disposal
- `goferMigrator.ts`: Detection + Orchestration + Resources + Paths

❌ **High Coupling**: Direct instantiation with `new`, global state

❌ **Low Cohesion**: Unrelated functions in same file

❌ **Difficult Testing**: Too many mocks needed, can't test parts in isolation

### After: Modular (Best Practices)

✅ **Single Responsibility**: Each service has one focused purpose

- `VersionDetector`: Only format detection
- `UpgradeService`: Only orchestration
- `ResourceSyncer`: Only file operations
- `PathMigrator`: Only path migration

✅ **Dependency Injection**: Container manages lifecycles, explicit dependencies

✅ **Facade Pattern**: `extension.ts` and `goferMigrator.ts` become thin
orchestrators

✅ **Testability**: Services tested independently with mocked dependencies

## Service Responsibilities

### Core Infrastructure (Phase 1)

| Service   | Responsibility                | LOC | Dependencies |
| --------- | ----------------------------- | --- | ------------ |
| Container | DI service registration       | 87  | TSyringe     |
| Logger    | Structured logging            | 147 | VSCode API   |

### Extension Services (Phase 3)

| Service        | Responsibility                  | LOC  | Dependencies         |
| -------------- | ------------------------------- | ---- | -------------------- |
| extension.ts   | Orchestrates activation         | ~800 | All services         |
| Disposal       | Resource cleanup                | ~200 | Logger               |
| EventHandlers  | Workspace event listeners       | ~200 | Logger               |
| Init           | Workspace initialization        | ~300 | Logger, Commands     |
| CommandRegistry| Command registration            | ~250 | Logger               |
| StateManager   | Global state management         | ~150 | Logger               |

### Migration Services (Phase 4)

| Service          | Responsibility                  | LOC  | Dependencies         |
| ---------------- | ------------------------------- | ---- | -------------------- |
| goferMigrator.ts | Facade for migration services   | 467  | All migration svcs   |
| VersionDetector  | Format detection                | 247  | Logger               |
| UpgradeService   | Upgrade orchestration           | 437  | Logger, Version      |
| ResourceSyncer   | File/resource sync              | 496  | Logger               |
| PathMigrator     | Path reference migration        | 332  | Logger               |

## Dependency Layers

### Layer 1: Foundation

- **Container**: Manages all service lifecycles
- **Logger**: Used by all services (zero dependencies)

### Layer 2: Core Services

- **StateManager**: Maintains extension state (depends: Logger)
- **DisposalService**: Cleans up resources (depends: Logger)

### Layer 3: Feature Services

- **Extension Services**: EventHandlers, InitializationService, CommandRegistry
  (depend: Logger)
- **Migration Services**: VersionDetector, UpgradeService, ResourceSyncer,
  PathMigrator (depend: Logger, VersionDetector)

### Layer 4: Facades

- **extension.ts**: Orchestrates extension lifecycle
- **goferMigrator.ts**: Orchestrates migration operations

## Benefits of Refactoring

### Code Quality

- ✅ **Reduced complexity**: Max 496 LOC per file vs. 2499 LOC
- ✅ **Improved cohesion**: Services have single, clear purpose
- ✅ **Better naming**: Service names describe responsibility

### Maintainability

- ✅ **Easier navigation**: Find code by service (e.g., "path migration" →
  `PathMigrator.ts`)
- ✅ **Isolated changes**: Update one service without touching others
- ✅ **Reduced merge conflicts**: Team works on different services

### Testing

- ✅ **Unit testable**: Mock dependencies via DI container
- ✅ **Integration testable**: Test service interactions
- ✅ **Faster tests**: Test one service at a time (not entire God object)

### Development Velocity

- ✅ **Parallel development**: Different developers on different services
- ✅ **Faster onboarding**: Understand one 300 LOC service vs. 2500 LOC file
- ✅ **Easier reviews**: 200-500 LOC PRs vs. 1000+ LOC changes

## Anti-Patterns Eliminated

### Before

1. **Blob/God Object**: 2499 LOC monolith
2. **Lava Flow**: Unclear which code is used
3. **Spaghetti Code**: Tangled control flow
4. **Golden Hammer**: Everything in one file

### After

1. **Single Responsibility**: Each service focused
2. **Dependency Injection**: Explicit dependencies
3. **Facade Pattern**: Thin orchestrators
4. **Service Layer**: Clean separation of concerns

## Future Phases

### Phase 2: Cache Services (Pending)

Will add:

- `SpecCache` (spec file caching)
- `MemoryCache` (memory indexing)

Both follow same pattern: <600 LOC, depend on Logger, registered in Container.

### Future Extraction Opportunities

If any service grows >500 LOC:

- Extract sub-services using same pattern
- Maintain <600 LOC limit per file
- Apply facade pattern if needed

